      <originalsloc id="aspace_ac3c5db4fc2e70521e14ff16b3c28f8f">
         <head>Existence and Location of Originals</head>
         <p>The entire collection can be located in the Architectural Drawings and Maps of Yale University Buildings and Grounds (RU 1).   The materials consist of design, preliminary, working, shop, and "as built" architectural drawings and maps of buildings and grounds owned or used by Yale University. The drawings range from original concepts to full scale details of equipment and ornamentation. The media vary from water colors, pen and ink sketches, pencil on tracing paper drawings to blueprints and photostats. Note: Forms part of Yale Record Group 46-A (YRG 46-A), Records and materials broadly documenting Yale buildings, facilities, and grounds.</p>
         <p>HM 203 only consists of Series I and is for staff use only.   Indexes by building, architect, date of drawing, and filming number are available in the repository for drawings in Series I.</p>  
      </originalsloc>
